== Sweet Potato Hash ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @sweet potato{1} into 3⁄4-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1} into 3⁄4-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and dice @onion{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Pick @sage{¼%oz} leaves from stems; mince until you have 1 TBSP.

Toss sweet potato, green pepper, and three-quarters of the onion on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, @fry seasoning{2%tsp}, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} (you'll use the rest of the fry seasoning later).

Roast on top rack until veggies are browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Buttermilk Biscuits ==

Lightly oil a second baking sheet. Remove @buttermilk biscuits{6%oz} from package; separate biscuits. Place on prepared sheet, spaced about 1 inch apart.

Bake on middle rack until golden brown, ~{7-10%minutes}.

== Pork Sausage Gravy ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining onion and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened and translucent, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove sausage from casing if necessary; discard casing. Stir in @Italian pork sausage mix{9%oz}, remaining @fry seasoning{1%tsp}, @brown sugar{2%tsp}, and @dried thyme{¾%tsp}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until sausage is browned and cooked through and onion is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 4 tsp brown sugar and 11⁄2 tsp thyme.

Stir sage, @cream sauce base{8%oz}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1} into pan with sausage mixture. Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low; stir in @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} until combined. (TIP: For thinner gravy, add a splash of water.) Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Fried Eggs ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a second large, preferably nonstick pan over medium-high heat. Crack @eggs{2} into pan and cover. (For 4 servings, you may need to cook eggs in batches.) Fry eggs to preference. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Halve biscuits. TIP: If necessary, warm gravy over medium-low heat, adding small splashes of water as needed.

> Pork Sausage is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Divide biscuits and hash between plates. Spoon as much gravy as you like over biscuits; top with fried eggs. Serve with any remaining gravy on the side.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.